{"title": "In a Syrian Saddle", "description": "A travelogue that chronicles the author's journey through Syria on horseback, considered one of the author's most notable works. Each chapter focuses on a different aspect of her journey. She provides vivid descriptions of the landscapes, people and customs she encounters along the way. One of the main themes of the book is the author's fascination with the Bedouin culture of Syria. Goodrich-Freer spends a significant amount of time with Bedouin tribes, learning about their customs and traditions. She also describes the challenges of traveling through a region that was often dangerous and unpredictable. Overall, In A Syrian Saddle is a fascinating account of a woman's journey through a land that was largely unknown to Westerners at the time. The book provides a unique perspective on the culture and history of Syria, and it remains a valuable resource for anyone interested in the region.  (Summary by Publisher)", "duration": 29237, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "19113", "name": "Ada Goodrich-Freer"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/inasyriansaddle_2601_librivox/inasyriansaddle_2601.jpg", "copyright_year": "1905", "genres": ["Modern (20th C)", "Exploration"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "PaulW"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "MaryAnn"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "sati"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Part 1 Chapter I - Going to Jericho", "readers": [18075], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/inasyriansaddle_2601_librivox/syriansaddle_01_goodrich-freer_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1340}, {"section": 2, "title": "Part 1 Chapter II - Stepping Eastward", "readers": [15829], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/inasyriansaddle_2601_librivox/syriansaddle_02_goodrich-freer_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2823}, {"section": 3, "title": "Part 1 Chapter III - Madaba", "readers": [16576], "path": "https://www.ar